track_notes: Hiked in 2022 August. This was similar to Castle Mountain approach, but a bit more difficult. Fallen trees were cleared recently. Trail was in good shape up to the pass. Only one huge tree which had to be climbed over. There is a sharp right turn after crossing the bridge. Then just follow the trail to the pass. Then cross-country navigation. I approached through the west slopes. It was more difficult then expected. This route had loose sand, ash, scree, also somewhat exposed class 3 climb on mixed quality rock. Mostly rotten slippery rocks unfortunately. Due to most of the west slope got burnt finding a good route was somewhat easier. Still ended up on steep bad terrain. There are rock outcrops and gullies which will slow or block your progress. Good summit area, with no register. Took me over 4 hours to summit with a light pack in running shoes. Boots recommended. I tried to hike out on the ridge, but ended up dropping down into the crater. A passable ridge route may exist though.
track_title: Via Trail 953 Crow Lake Way and west slopes
